{
  "stem": "9701.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And at midnight, when the motors were all revved up, and the boat was ready to leave, though, we were told we should not leave our cabin, I went up on deck, and I think there was a little waterfall up there.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And the following morning, I discovered, and it said, men and women.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I was so single-minded on water closet or WC, that even though I might have seen that, it didn't register.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I knew what those two words meant.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In Harwich, we boarded a train to London, to London's Liverpool Street Station.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there, we were taken to a huge hall.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there were people there waiting for to receive those of us who had arrived.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Some of the children went into private homes or foster homes.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This went into institutional settings.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I went into a private home, a Jewish home.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The way that I was able to go to England is my father, in his research looking for people who could sponsor our exit from Germany, found a cousin of my grandfather's, my mother's father's cousin, a woman by the name of Anna, A-N-N-A, Simon, S-I-M-O-N.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "She was in her 70s at the time, and she had come to England when she was about 18 months old.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And she agreed to sponsor me but was not willing to sponsor my parents [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] because I guess it would have meant too much of a financial responsibility for her.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And she did not want me to stay at her home.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "She was still working in her own business at that time, and actually had very little contact with me.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Most of it was with her-- it was through her daughter, Beatrice Mayer, B-E-A-T-R-I-C-E.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Mayer is M-A-Y-E-R.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
